e, "mention": "SYCP3", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9806181788444519, "span": {"begin": 472, "end": 477}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2565"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "&gamma", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8890489339828491, "span": {"begin": 482, "end": 488}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3014"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": ";H2AX", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8665134906768799, "span": {"begin": 488, "end": 493}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:346673"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Stra8", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9922735095024109, "span": {"begin": 641, "end": 646}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9851354956626892, "span": {"begin": 682, "end": 686}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "humans", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9911298751831055, "span": {"begin": 690, "end": 696}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "oocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7439165115356445, "span": {"begin": 837, "end": 844}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "oocyte pool", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6077619791030884, "span": {"begin": 906, "end": 917}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "oogonia", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8065744042396545, "span": {"begin": 1006, "end": 1013}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:346673"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Stra8", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9941165447235107, "span": {"begin": 1044, "end": 1049}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.936327338218689, "span": {"begin": 1055, "end": 1059}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:346673"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Stra8", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9963346719741821, "span": {"begin": 1086, "end": 1091}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9579355120658875, "span": {"begin": 1104, "end": 1108}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "oocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.801673412322998, "span": {"begin": 1179, "end": 1186}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:346673"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Stra8", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9823018312454224, "span": {"begin": 1192, "end": 1197}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "oogonia", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.804375171661377, "span": {"begin": 1259, "end": 1266}}, {"id": ["mesh:D014212"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "atRA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.937188446521759, "span": {"begin": 1297, "end": 1301}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9585806131362915, "span": {"begin": 1318, "end": 1322}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "humans", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9889583587646484, "span": {"begin": 1450, "end": 1456}}], "text": "Oocyte meiosis  Oogonia, the female germ cells, are the precursors for the female oocytes. Primary oocytes are formed in the ovaries during fetal development when oogonia enter into prophase I of meiosis; meiotic entry initiates at around embryonic (E) day 13.5 in mice, E15.5 in rats, and gestational week 10-12 in humans. The entry into meiosis is driven by expression of the key genes Stra8, Meiosin and Rec8 and is followed by expression of meiotic proteins including SYCP3 and &gamma;H2AX (Baltus et al, 2006; Bowles et al, 2006; Ishiguro et al, 2020; Kojima et al, 2019; Koubova et al, 2014; Spiller et al, 2017). The crucial role for Stra8 in meiotic entry is conserved from mice to humans (Childs et al, 2011).  Disrupted meiotic entry as Key Event  The initiation of meiosis during fetal life is critical for maintenance of the oocytes throughout development and, eventually, for establishing the oocyte pool, or &lsquo;oocyte reserve&rsquo; at birth. Without timely fetal entry into meiosis, the oogonia are depleted, as evidenced in Stra8-null mice (Baltus et al, 2006). The Stra8-null female mice are infertile and display abnormally small ovaries that are devoid of oocytes. For Stra8 to be expressed and, therefore, for meiosis to initiate, the oogonia require direct stimulation by atRA as evidenced in mice (Bowles et al, 2016; Bowles et al, 2006; Feng et al, 2021; Koubova et al, 2006; Spiller et al, 2017; Teletin et al, 2017), and humans (Childs et al, 2011; Le Bouffant et al, 2010).", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 21:52:34 +0000 2026"}